01/22/82  forum request:  chairman, cm

Syntax:  cm {meeting} {-control_args}


Syntax as an active request:  [cm {meeting}]


Function:
   Prints/returns the user_id (Person_id.Project_id) of the
   chairman of the specified meeting, or changes the chairman 
   of the current meeting. If no arguments are given, the
   name of the chairman of the current meeting is printed.


Argument:
meeting
   is the name or pathname of a forum meeting.

Control Arguments:
-force, -fc
   tells forum not to ask if the chairman should be changed.
-set new_chairman
   changes the chairman of the current meeting. new_chairman must
   be of the form Person_id.Project_id. Only the current chairman
   may change the chairman.
